📘 1 & 2 CHRONICLES — 300 QUESTIONS (RSV)
With Chapter & Verse References
PART 1 — OBJECTIVE QUESTIONS (200)
1 Chronicles 1–9 (Genealogies)
1. According to 1 Chronicles 1:1, who was the first man listed in the genealogy from Adam?
a) Seth
b) Adam
c) Enosh
d) Cain

2. 1 Chronicles 1:4 names Noah, Shem, Ham, and who as the sons of Noah?
a) Japheth
b) Canaan
c) Arpachshad
d) Eber

3. According to 1 Chronicles 1:10, Nimrod was a mighty warrior on the earth. He was the son of whom?
a) Ham
b) Cush
c) Shem
d) Egypt

4. 1 Chronicles 1:17 lists the sons of Shem: Elam, Asshur, Arpachshad, Lud, and Aram. Who is also included?
a) Eber
b) Peleg
c) Uz
d) Joktan

5. According to 1 Chronicles 1:19, the earth was divided in the days of Peleg. Peleg’s brother was whom?
a) Reu
b) Serug
c) Joktan
d) Nahor

6. 1 Chronicles 1:34 says Abraham was the father of Isaac. Isaac’s sons were Esau and whom?
a) Jacob
b) Israel
c) Ishmael
d) Laban

7. According to 1 Chronicles 2:1-2, how many sons did Israel (Jacob) have?
a) 10
b) 12
c) 14
d) 6

8. 1 Chronicles 2:3 says Judah’s firstborn was Er, who was wicked in the sight of the Lord. What happened to him?
a) He was exiled
b) He was killed by the Lord
c) He repented
d) He became a leader

9. According to 1 Chronicles 2:7, Achan (called Achar) troubled Israel by taking what devoted thing?
a) Gold
b) Silver
c) A robe
d) All of the above

10. 1 Chronicles 2:15 says David was the seventh son of Jesse. Who was David’s oldest brother?
a) Eliab
b) Abinadab
c) Shammah
d) Nethane

11. According to 1 Chronicles 3:1-4, how many sons were born to David in Hebron?
a) 3
b) 6
c) 7
d) 10

12. 1 Chronicles 3:5 names four sons born to David in Jerusalem by Bathsheba. Which of the following is NOT among them?
a) Shimea
b) Shobab
c) Nathan
d) Solomon

13. According to 1 Chronicles 3:16, the sons of Jehoiakim (also called Coniah) included Zedekiah and whom?
a) Jehoahaz
b) Jeconiah
c) Shallum
d) Josiah

14. 1 Chronicles 4:9-10 records the prayer of Jabez. What did he ask God for?
a) Riches
b) Protection from harm
c) Enlargement of territory
d) All of the above

15. According to 1 Chronicles 4:10, God granted Jabez what he asked because Jabez was more what than his brothers?
a) Faithful
b) Righteous
c) Honorable
d) Wise

16. 1 Chronicles 5:1 says Reuben lost his birthright because he defiled his father’s bed. To whom was the birthright given?
a) Joseph
b) Judah
c) Levi
d) Simeon

17. According to 1 Chronicles 5:2, though Judah became the ruling tribe, the birthright belonged to whom?
a) Judah
b) Joseph
c) Reuben
d) Levi

18. 1 Chronicles 5:18-22 says the Reubenites, Gadites, and half-tribe of Manasseh waged war against which people?
a) Moabites
b) Ammonites
c) Hagrites
d) Edomites

19. According to 1 Chronicles 6:1, the sons of Levi were Gershom, Kohath, and whom?
a) Aaron
b) Moses
c) Merari
d) Eleazar

20. 1 Chronicles 6:49 says Aaron and his sons were appointed to burn incense on the altar of burnt offering and to make atonement for Israel. This refers to their role as what?
a) Prophets
b) Priests
c) Judges
d) Elders

21. According to 1 Chronicles 9:1, “All Israel were enrolled by genealogies” and these records were found in what book?
a) The Book of the Kings of Israel
b) The Book of the Kings of Judah
c) The Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel and Judah
d) The Book of the Law

22. 1 Chronicles 9:2 says the first to dwell in their possessions in their cities were Israelites, priests, Levites, and what?
a) The gatekeepers
b) The singers
c) The temple servants (Nethinim)
d) The elders

23. According to 1 Chronicles 9:20, Phinehas the son of Eleazar was the ruler over whom?
a) The singers
b) The gatekeepers
c) The Levites
d) The priests

1 Chronicles 10 — The Death of Saul
24. According to 1 Chronicles 10:2, the Philistines killed Saul’s three sons. What were their names?
a) Jonathan, Abinadab, Malchishua
b) Jonathan, Ishui, Eshbaal
c) Abinadab, Malchishua, Armoni
d) Jonathan, Mephibosheth, Abinadab

25. 1 Chronicles 10:4 says Saul asked his armor-bearer to kill him because he feared what?
a) The Philistines
b) Torture
c) The uncircumcised would mock him
d) Capture

