a) Idolatry and murder
b) Unfaithfulness to the Lord and consulting a medium
c) Pride and greed
d) Disobedience to Samuel and sparing Agag

28. According to 1 Chronicles 10:14, the Lord slew Saul and turned his kingdom over to whom?
a) Solomon
b) David the son of Jesse
c) Ish-bosheth
d) Abner

1 Chronicles 11 — David Becomes King
29. According to 1 Chronicles 11:1-2, all Israel came to David at Hebron and said, “We are your bone and flesh. In times past, even when Saul was king, you were the leader of Israel. And the Lord your God said to you, ‘You shall be shepherd of my people Israel, and you shall be what?’”
a) King over Israel
b) Prince over my people Israel
c) Ruler over my inheritance
d) Commander of the army

30. According to 1 Chronicles 11:3, David made a covenant with the elders of Israel at Hebron, and they anointed him king over Israel. This fulfilled the word of the Lord by whom?
a) Moses
b) Samuel
c) Nathan
d) Gad

31. 1 Chronicles 11:5 records David’s first military action as king: he took the stronghold of Zion, which became known as what?
a) Jerusalem
b) The City of David
