35. According to 1 Chronicles 11:22-23, Benaiah son of Jehoiada killed a lion in a pit on what day?
a) A rainy day
b) A snowy day
c) A sabbath day
d) A hot day

1 Chronicles 12 — David’s Supporters
36. According to 1 Chronicles 12:2, some of David’s mighty men were armed with bows and could shoot arrows and sling stones with which hand?
a) Right hand
b) Left hand
c) Both hands
d) Either hand

37. 1 Chronicles 12:8 says that the Gadites who joined David in the wilderness had faces like lions and were swift as what?
a) Eagles
b) Gazelles on the mountains
c) Horses
d) The wind

38. According to 1 Chronicles 12:18, the Spirit came upon Amasai, who declared, “We are yours, O David; and with you, O son of Jesse! Peace, peace to you, and peace to your helpers! For your God helps you.” Amasai was a chief of whom?
a) The Gadites
b) The Thirty
c) The Benjaminites
d) The Levites

39. According to 1 Chronicles 12:32, the men of Issachar had understanding of what?
a) The law of Moses
b) The times, to know what Israel ought to do
c) The plan of battle
d) The prophecies of the seers

