a) The house of Obed-edom the Gittite
b) The house of Abinadab
c) The tabernacle at Gibeon
d) The city of Bethlehem

1 Chronicles 14 — David’s House and Victories
46. According to 1 Chronicles 14:1, which king sent cedar logs, masons, and carpenters to build a house for David?
a) Pharaoh of Egypt
b) Hiram of Tyre
c) Toi of Hamath
d) Hadadezer of Zobah

