d) Cedar trees

1 Chronicles 15 — The Ark Brought to Jerusalem
51. According to 1 Chronicles 15:2, David said that only whom might carry the ark of God?
a) The priests
b) The Levites
c) The Kohathites
d) The elders

52. 1 Chronicles 15:12 says David told the priests and Levites to sanctify themselves to bring up the ark, because the Lord had chosen them to do what?
a) Sing before the ark
b) Minister to him forever
c) Carry the ark and minister to him
d) Guard the tabernacle

53. According to 1 Chronicles 15:16, David told the chiefs of the Levites to appoint their brethren as singers with musical instruments, including harps, lyres, and what?
a) Trumpets
b) Cymbals
c) Drums
d) Flutes

54. 1 Chronicles 15:20 names Zechariah, Aziel, Shemiramoth, Jehiel, Unni, Eliab, Maaseiah, and Benaiah assigned to what instrument?
a) Trumpets
b) Lyres according to Alamoth
c) Harps according to Sheminith
d) Cymbals

55. According to 1 Chronicles 15:27, David wore a robe of fine linen, as did all the Levites who carried the ark, and David also wore what?
a) A golden crown
b) A linen ephod
c) A priestly breastplate
d) A royal scepter

56. According to 1 Chronicles 15:28, the entire house of Israel brought up the ark with shouting, with the sound of the horn, trumpets, and cymbals, and with music on what?
