d) Shofars and bells

1 Chronicles 16 — The Ark in Jerusalem
57. According to 1 Chronicles 16:1, after the ark was placed in the tent David had pitched for it, what did they offer before God?
a) Prayers
b) Burnt offerings and peace offerings
c) Tithes
d) Incense

58. 1 Chronicles 16:4 says David appointed certain Levites to minister before the ark, to invoke, to thank, and to praise the Lord, the God of Israel. Who was the chief among them?
a) Heman
b) Asaph
c) Ethan
d) Jeduthun

59. According to 1 Chronicles 16:7, on that day David first appointed that thanks be given to the Lord by Asaph and his brethren. This marks the beginning of what?
a) The temple music
b) The psalms of David
c) The Levitical choir
d) Psalm 105

60. 1 Chronicles 16:11 says, “Seek the Lord and his strength, seek his presence continually!” What is the preceding command in verse 10?
a) Sing to the Lord
b) Glory in his holy name
c) Let the hearts of those who seek the Lord rejoice
d) Remember his wonderful works

61. According to 1 Chronicles 16:15, “He is mindful of his covenant forever, of the word that he commanded, for a thousand generations.” This refers to the covenant with whom?
a) Moses
b) Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob
c) David
d) Noah

62. According to 1 Chronicles 16:22, “Touch not my anointed ones, do my prophets no harm.” This warning is addressed to whom?
a) Kings and nations
b) The Philistines
c) Israel’s enemies
d) The pagans

63. 1 Chronicles 16:23 says, “Sing to the Lord, all the earth! Tell of his salvation from day to day.” What follows in verse 24?
a) Declare his glory among the nations
b) For great is the Lord
c) Honor and majesty are before him
d) Worship the Lord in holy array

64. According to 1 Chronicles 16:29, “Ascribe to the Lord the glory due his name; bring an offering and come before him! Worship the Lord in holy array” or alternatively what?
a) In the beauty of holiness
b) In the court of the Lord
c) With timbrel and dance
d) At his footstool

65. 1 Chronicles 16:34 records a refrain repeated often in the Psalms: “O give thanks to the Lord, for he is good; for his steadfast love endures forever!” This same verse appears exactly in which Psalm?
a) Psalm 100
b) Psalm 106:1
c) Psalm 23
d) Psalm 119

1 Chronicles 17 — God’s Covenant with David
66. According to 1 Chronicles 17:1, when David was living in his house, he said to Nathan the prophet, “I dwell in a house of cedar, but the ark of the covenant of the Lord is under what?”
a) A tent
b) A curtain
c) A shelter
d) A tabernacle of curtains

67. According to 1 Chronicles 17:4, the word of the Lord came to Nathan saying, “Go and tell my servant David, ‘Thus says the Lord: You shall not build me a house to dwell in. For I have not dwelt in a house since the day I led Israel up until this day, but I have gone from tent to tent and from one dwelling to another. In all places where I have moved with all Israel, did I speak a word with any of the judges of Israel, whom I commanded to shepherd my people, saying, “Why have you not built me a house of what?”’”

a) Stone
b) Cedar
c) Gold
d) Great cost

68. According to 1 Chronicles 17:11-12, what did the Lord promise David regarding his son?
a) He will build a house for my name
b) He will be mighty in battle
c) He will reign forever
d) He will see the temple completed

69. 1 Chronicles 17:13 says, “I will be his father, and he shall be my son; I will not take my steadfast love from him as I took it from him who was before you.” Who was “him who was before you”?
a) Saul
