a) They were exiled
b) They died before their father
c) They became high priests
d) They served in Gibeon

102. According to 1 Chronicles 24:3-4, David and Zadok (of Eleazar’s sons) and Ahimelech (of Ithamar’s sons) organized them. The sons of Eleazar had how many more chiefs than the sons of Ithamar?
a) 8 more
b) 12 more
c) 16 more
d) 4 more

103. According to 1 Chronicles 24:7-18, how many priestly divisions (courses) were established by lot?
a) 12
b) 24
c) 48
d) 36

104. According to 1 Chronicles 24:19, this arrangement for the priests was to ensure they could enter the house of the Lord according to the ordinance given through whom?
a) Moses
b) Aaron
c) David
d) Samuel

1 Chronicles 25 — Divisions of the Musicians
105. According to 1 Chronicles 25:1, David and the chiefs of the service set apart for the service those who prophesied with lyres, harps, and cymbals. Who were these men?
a) The priests
b) The sons of Asaph, Heman, and Jeduthun
c) The gatekeepers
d) The temple servants

106. According to 1 Chronicles 25:5, Heman had how many sons and daughters given to him by God to raise up his horn?
a) 6 sons and 6 daughters
b) 14 sons and 3 daughters
c) 12 sons and 3 daughters
d) 20 sons and 10 daughters

107. According to 1 Chronicles 25:7, the number of skilled musicians trained in singing to the Lord (with their brethren) was how many?
a) 144
b) 200
c) 288
d) 400

