1 Chronicles 28 — David’s Charge to Solomon
117. According to 1 Chronicles 28:2, David rose to his feet and said, “Hear me, my brethren and my people. I had it in my heart to build a house of rest for the ark of the covenant of the Lord and for the footstool of our God, and I made preparations for building. But God said to me, ‘You shall not build a house for my name because you are a man of war and have shed blood.’” What did God call the temple?
a) A house of prayer
b) A house of rest
c) A house of sacrifice
d) A house of glory

118. According to 1 Chronicles 28:6, the Lord said to David, “Solomon your son shall build my house and my courts, for I have chosen him to be my son, and I will be his father, and I will establish his kingdom forever if he continues in my commandments and my ordinances, as at this day.” What is the condition?
a) His wealth
b) His wisdom
c) His obedience
d) His peace

