a) Thunderstorm
b) The Shekinah presence of God
c) Incense from the altar
d) Smoke from the sacrifices

2 Chronicles 6 — Solomon’s Prayer of Dedication
159. According to 2 Chronicles 6:12-13, Solomon stood before the altar in the presence of all the assembly and spread out his hands. He had made a bronze platform 5 cubits long, 5 cubits wide, and 3 cubits high on which he knelt. This was his posture of what?
a) Authority
b) Humility and prayer
c) Judgment
d) Blessing

160. According to 2 Chronicles 6:18, Solomon prayed, “But will God indeed dwell with man on the earth? Behold, heaven and the highest heaven cannot contain you; how much less this house which I have built!” This emphasizes what truth about God?
a) God is far away
b) God is transcendent and cannot be confined
c) The temple is useless
d) God only dwells in heaven

161. According to 2 Chronicles 6:22-23, Solomon asked that God judge between his servants, condemning the guilty and vindicating the righteous. This is a prayer for justice in cases of what?
a) Theft
b) Oaths before the altar
