d) Idolatry

162. According to 2 Chronicles 6:26-27, Solomon prayed for the nation when there is drought because the people have sinned. He asked God to hear in heaven, forgive the sin, and what?
a) Send rain
b) Heal the land
c) Teach them the good way
d) All of the above

163. According to 2 Chronicles 6:32-33, Solomon prayed for the foreigner who comes from a far country for the sake of the great name of the Lord. He asked that God do whatever the foreigner calls to him for, so that all the peoples of the earth may know God’s name and fear him. This shows what?
a) The temple was for Israel only
b) God’s concern for all nations
c) Foreigners were unwelcome
d) Solomon’s political strategy

164. According to 2 Chronicles 6:36-39, Solomon acknowledged that all people sin. He prayed that when Israel is taken captive to a foreign land, if they repent with all their heart and soul, God would hear and forgive. This prayer anticipated what future event?
a) The exile to Babylon
b) The destruction of the temple
c) The coming of the Messiah
d) The Assyrian invasion

