169. According to 2 Chronicles 8:3-4, Solomon went to Hamath-zobah and took it. He also built Tadmor in the wilderness and what other store cities?
a) Megiddo and Gezer
b) Beth-horon and Baalath
c) Hazor and Jericho
d) Dan and Beersheba

170. According to 2 Chronicles 8:11, Solomon brought Pharaoh’s daughter (his wife) out of the city of David to a house he built for her because he said, “My wife shall not live in the house of David king of Israel, for the places where the ark of the Lord has come are holy.” This shows what?
a) Solomon’s respect for holiness
b) Solomon’s shame at marrying a foreigner
c) Political expediency
d) Rejection of his wife

171. According to 2 Chronicles 8:18, Hiram sent Solomon ships and servants who knew the sea. They went to Ophir and brought how many talents of gold to Solomon?
a) 120 talents
b) 450 talents
c) 666 talents
d) 1,000 talents

2 Chronicles 9 — The Queen of Sheba and Solomon’s Wealth
172. According to 2 Chronicles 9:1, the Queen of Sheba came to Jerusalem to test Solomon with hard questions. She came with a very great retinue, with camels bearing spices, gold, and precious stones. What did she hear about Solomon?
a) His wisdom
b) His wealth
c) His fame
d) All of the above

173. According to 2 Chronicles 9:2-4, when the Queen saw Solomon’s wisdom, the house he built, the food of his table, the seating of his officials, their attire, his cupbearers, and the burnt offerings he offered at the house of the Lord, what happened?
a) She was jealous
b) There was no more spirit in her
c) She converted to worship the Lord
d) She asked for a treaty

174. According to 2 Chronicles 9:6, the Queen said to Solomon, “The report was true which I heard in my own land of your affairs and of your wisdom, but I did not believe the reports until I came and my own eyes had seen it. Behold, half the greatness of your wisdom was not told me; you surpass the report which I heard.” What did she call Solomon’s servants?
a) Blessed
b) Happy
c) Wise
d) Fortunate

175. According to 2 Chronicles 9:9, the Queen gave Solomon 120 talents of gold, a very great quantity of spices, and precious stones. What did Solomon give her in return?
a) Nothing
b) All that she desired, besides what she had brought
c) A treaty of peace
d) Gold and silver

176. According to 2 Chronicles 9:13-14, the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was how many talents?
a) 420
b) 666
c) 1,000
d) 2,000

