177. According to 2 Chronicles 10:4, the people of Israel said to Rehoboam (Solomon’s son), “Your father made our yoke heavy. Now therefore lighten the hard service of your father and his heavy yoke upon us, and we will serve you.” What was the yoke?
a) Military conscription
b) Heavy taxes and forced labor
c) Religious obligations
d) Foreign alliances

178. According to 2 Chronicles 10:8, Rehoboam forsook the counsel of the old men and took counsel with the young men who had grown up with him. What did the young men advise?
a) Lighten the yoke
b) Speak harshly and make the yoke heavier
c) Give them freedom
d) Go to war

179. According to 2 Chronicles 10:11, Rehoboam told the people, “My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with what?”
a) Chains
b) Scorpions
c) Fire
d) Swords

180. According to 2 Chronicles 10:16, when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, they answered, “What portion have we in David? We have no inheritance in the son of Jesse. Each of you go to your tents, O Israel!” Who was left as king only over Judah?
a) Jeroboam
b) Rehoboam
c) Abijah
d) Asa

181. According to 2 Chronicles 10:19, Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this day. This event marks the division of the kingdom. Who became king over the northern tribes (Israel)?
