b) Nadab
c) Baasha
d) Omri

2 Chronicles 11 — Rehoboam Fortifies Judah
182. According to 2 Chronicles 11:1, Rehoboam assembled 180,000 chosen warriors from Judah and Benjamin to fight against Israel and restore the kingdom. However, the word of the Lord came to whom saying, “You shall not go up nor fight against your brethren?”
a) Rehoboam
b) Shemaiah the man of God
c) Jeroboam
d) Azariah the prophet

183. According to 2 Chronicles 11:5-10, Rehoboam built fortified cities in Judah, including Bethlehem, Etam, Tekoa, and others. How many cities did he fortify?
a) 5
b) 10
c) 15
d) 20

184. According to 2 Chronicles 11:13-14, the priests and Levites from all Israel (the northern kingdom) resettled in Judah because Jeroboam and his sons had rejected them from serving as priests to the Lord. Jeroboam also appointed his own priests for what?
a) The golden calves
b) The high places
c) The demons and the calves he had made
d) The Asherah poles

185. According to 2 Chronicles 11:16-17, those who set their hearts to seek the Lord God of Israel came to Jerusalem to sacrifice, and they strengthened the kingdom of Judah for three years. After three years, what did Rehoboam do?
a) He became faithful
b) He forsook the law of the Lord
c) He built the temple
d) He made peace with Israel

